               </p>
               <p xml:space="preserve">The mountains surrounding the town provide natural water sources and provide room for the region’s flora and fauna. Additionally, they accommodate ancient ruins which provide insights into regional history.</p>
               <p rendition="#slideshow">
                  <figure>
                     <link target="DAHMANI-RIF-Ausflug-nach-Mdayna-8-scaled.jpg"/>
                     <graphic url="thumb/DAHMANI-RIF-Ausflug-nach-Mdayna-8-scaled.jpg"/>
                     <head>Natural water ressource</head>
                  </figure>
                  <figure>
                     <link target="IMG_20190917_103739099.jpg"/>
                     <graphic url="thumb/IMG_20190917_103739099.jpg"/>
                     <head>Flowers growing on the hill</head>
                  </figure>
                  <figure>
                     <link target="IMG_20190917_111937415_HDR.jpg"/>
                     <graphic url="thumb/IMG_20190917_111937415_HDR.jpg"/>
                     <head>Lizard hidden in a stone opening</head>
                  </figure>
                  <figure>
                     <link target="IMG_20190917_103054463.jpg"/>
                     <graphic url="thumb/IMG_20190917_103054463.jpg"/>
                     <head>Snail at the Ebba hill</head>
                  </figure>
                  <figure>
                     <link target="IMG_20190917_120339241.jpg"/>
                     <graphic url="thumb/IMG_20190917_120339241.jpg"/>
                     <head>Mushrooms on the Ebba hill</head>
                  </figure>
                  <figure>
                     <link target="IMG_20190917_112116187.jpg"/>
                     <graphic url="thumb/IMG_20190917_112116187.jpg"/>
                     <head>On top of the Ebba hill</head>
                  </figure>
                  <figure>
                     <link target="IMG_20190917_111110031.jpg"/>
                     <graphic url="thumb/IMG_20190917_111110031.jpg"/>
                     <head>Ebba's ruins</head>
                  </figure>
               </p>
               <p> Enclosed between this mountain area called Ebba, which means “market” in the Phoenician language, and the Roman Ksour Hilla (Qṣūr Hilla), “castles of Hilla”, Dahmani used to be called Ebba Ksour in previous times. This name remained until 1973 when the town was renamed after the medieval local saint Sidi Dahmani (Sīdi id-Dahmǟni).</p>
               <p>
                  <figure rendition="#full-width">
                     <link target="IMG_20190917_102745560.jpg"/>
                     <graphic url="IMG_20190917_102745560.jpg"/>
                     <head>On top of the Ebba hill</head>
                  </figure>
               </p>
